climbs.name: A Guy Walks Into a Canyon

content.description:
The problem climbs bullet stone over a perfect landing via enjoyable movement.

Sit start matched on the horizontal rail. From there, traverse left along the rail to a great sidepull, mantel with the right hand, achieve a high right foot, use a double-dimple right hand undercling, position the feet, make a committing move to the lip, reel in the barn door, and mantel on top.

Is it an eliminate? I'm not sure. I first thought that the feature used on

What Will They Think

would have to be intentionally avoided, but the problem climbed naturally without doing so. Bottom line, it didn't feel forced.
content.protection: A pad or two. The landing is perfect though.
content.location: It climbs the east face of Regal Rock.
